snippet.title: Trump ambushes South African president with video compilation alleging 'genocide' in South Africa
snippet.description:
Donald Trump has ambushed South African President Cyril Ramaphosa during a meeting at the White House by playing videos which he claimed pertained to allegations of genocide in South Africa.

The US president was hosting the South African leader, who sat quietly while the footage was played, and Mr Ramaphosa later said: "I'd like to know where that is because this [the videos] I've never seen".

Videos were shown of South African officials allegedly calling for violence against white farmers.

snippet.title: In full: Trump and Musk meet South African president in Oval Office
snippet.description:
Donald Trump is hosting Cyril Ramaphosa, the South African president, at the White House in a bid to reset relations between the two countries after months of tensions.

The meeting comes after Mr Trump accused Pretoria of carrying out a “genocide” against white Afrikaner farmers, allegations South Africa has vehemently denied.

Earlier this month the Trump administration welcomed 59 white South Africans as refugees who have claimed they have been discriminated against because of their race.

Mr Ramaphosa has said those arriving in the US are “cowards” and “do not fit the bill” for refugees.

snippet.title: Shandesh - Mamenemene (feat. DJ Janisto & King Salah)
snippet.description:
Shandesh is back and bolder than ever with her latest release, “Mamenemene”, a raw and 
unfiltered anthem that calls out the snakes in the grass. The term mamenemene refers to 
two-faced individuals, those who pretend to support you but secretly root for your downfall. 
With its sharp lyrics, high-energy production, and streetwise message, this single is an 
unapologetic ode to resilience and reality. 
Following the massive success of her breakout hit “Sdudla or Slender, which recently 
crossed 10 million streams across platforms, Shandesh is cementing her place as one of 
the most vital new voices in the South African music scene. Her unique sound is redefining 
the Lekompo genre, a rapidly growing subculture that fuses Bolo House, Kwaito, and trap
inspired production with bold township storytelling. 
“Mamenemene” is a message to every dreamer who’s had to hustle through envy, fake love, 
and backhanded praise. Shandesh’s unmistakable vocal style, confident delivery, and lyrical 
grit make this one of the most relatable and hard-hitting records in the genre right now. 
With each release, Shandesh is pushing Lekompo into new spaces, bridging grassroots 
authenticity with national mainstream appeal, all while flying the flag for fierce, unapologetic 
women in music. 

Thank you for watching. 
Please subscribe to support the channel.

unapologetic ode to resilience and reality. 
Following the massive success of her breakout hit “Sdudla or Slender, which recently 
crossed 10 million streams across platforms, Shandesh is cementing her place as one of 
the most vital new voices in the South African music scene. Her unique sound is redefining 
the Lekompo genre, a rapidly growing subculture that fuses Bolo House, Kwaito, and trap
inspired production with bold township storytelling. 
“Mamenemene” is a message to every dreamer who’s had to hustle through envy, fake love, 
and backhanded praise. Shandesh’s unmistakable vocal style, confident delivery, and lyrical 
grit make this one of the most relatable and hard-hitting records in the genre right now. 
With each release, Shandesh is pushing Lekompo into new spaces, bridging grassroots 
authenticity with national mainstream appeal, all while flying the flag for fierce, unapologetic 
women in music.
